{"type":"text","timestamp":1775888313729,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b30688c001Ib9hWbjf0gv2jh","messageID":"msg_d7b303b80001uXM2xMGzDyymtm","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","type":"text","text":"I'll create a delta-spec.md file for AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 based on the base specs provided.","time":{"start":1775888313726,"end":1775888313726}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888313758,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b312d820019cNoQBTjOhH2M7","messageID":"msg_d7b303b80001uXM2xMGzDyymtm","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-240a459167f74e899f07fce78ebdafb0","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification — AR-036 Dify Plugin Integration\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplementation deltas for adding Dify plugin integration to the AgentCube project, including the Python SDK client library and PCAP analyzer example application.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Create Dify plugin package structure\n\nThe system SHALL create a complete Dify plugin package under `integrations/dify-plugin/` with all required manifest files, provider descriptors, tool definitions, and Python implementations.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin directory layout exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a new `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n- **WHEN** the package structure is created\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement plugin manifest\n\nThe system SHALL implement `manifest.yaml` with all required fields including version, type, author, name, multilingual labels/descriptions, icons, resource permissions, tool provider references, and runner metadata.\n\n#### Scenario: Manifest contains all required fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the file is parsed by Dify toolchain\n- **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version: 0.0.2`, `type: plugin`, `author: volcano-sh`, `name: agentcube`, `label` with multilingual map for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR`, `description` with multilingual strings, `icon: icon.png`, `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`, `resource` subtree with `memory` and `permission` flags, `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`, and `meta` with `version`, `arch` (amd64, arm64), `runner` (language: python, version: \"3.12\", entrypoint: main), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement provider descriptor\n\nThe system SHALL implement `provider/agentcube.yaml` with identity fields and tool list pointing to the code interpreter tool.\n\n#### Scenario: Provider descriptor structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the provider is loaded by Dify\n- **THEN** the file SHALL contain `identity` with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label`, multilingual `description`, `icon`, a `tools` list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement tool schema\n\nThe system SHALL implement `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` with the complete parameter schema for the code interpreter integration.\n\n#### Scenario: Tool parameter schema\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the tool is configured in Dify\n- **THEN** the schema SHALL define `identity` with `name: agentcube-code-interpreter`, `author: agentcube`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `parameters` array with `router_url` (string, required, form), `workload_manager_url` (string, required, form), `language` (select, options: python, javascript, typescript, llm), `code` (string, llm), `command` (string, llm), `session_id` (string, llm), `session_reuse` (boolean, llm), and `code_interpreter_id` (string, llm), each with `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, and `form` fields\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement plugin main entry\n\nThe system SHALL implement `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a 120-second request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n- **WHEN** Dify starts the plugin\n- **THEN** the file SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement provider class\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class that extends `ToolProvider` with credential validation.\n\n#### Scenario: Provider class structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n- **WHEN** the provider class is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)` with `_validate_credentials` method that may raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement tool class\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` class that extends `Tool` and delegates to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: Tool class invocation\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n- **WHEN** Dify invokes the tool\n- **THEN** the class SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)` with `_invoke` method that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`, and an `execute` method accepting `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`, and delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create plugin dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with pinned versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk`.\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n- **THEN** the file SHALL contain `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create Python SDK package\n\nThe system SHALL create the complete `agentcube-sdk` Python package under `sdk-python/` with all client classes and utilities.\n\n#### Scenario: SDK package layout\n\n- **GIVEN** `sdk-python/` directory\n- **WHEN** the SDK is structured\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `pyproject.toml`, `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/exceptions.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/utils/http.py`, `agentcube/utils/utils.py`, `agentcube/utils/log.py`, and `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterClient` with session management, file operations, code execution, and command execution.\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL accept `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url` (or from `ROUTER_URL` env), `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id`, initialize `ControlPlaneClient` and `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and raise `ValueError` if `router_url` is not provided\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance used as context manager\n- **WHEN** the context exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` which closes the data plane session, deletes the control plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Command execution with non-zero exit\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called\n- **WHEN** the remote command returns `exit_code != 0`\n- **THEN** the method SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` as `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n- **WHEN** the code is executed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` with session bootstrap, invocation, and lifecycle management.\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization and session bootstrap\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated without `session_id`\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`, raising `ValueError` if the header is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session\n\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance with falsy `session_id`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement ControlPlaneClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `ControlPlaneClient` with session creation and deletion via the Workload Manager API.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session\n\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, and `metadata`, and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session with 404\n\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called and server returns 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with file operations, command execution, and code execution via the Router API.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with timeout buffer\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=<value>)` posts to `api/execute`\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON with `command` array and `timeout` string, and the read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n\n#### Scenario: File write operation\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode: \"0644\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with session bootstrap and invocation via the Router API.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to 120\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement exception hierarchy\n\nThe system SHALL define the complete exception hierarchy in `agentcube/exceptions.py`.\n\n#### Scenario: Exception classes defined\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n- **WHEN** exceptions are imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentCubeError` (base), `CommandExecutionError` (with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`), `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement utility modules\n\nThe system SHALL implement utility modules for HTTP session creation, token reading, and logging.\n\n#### Scenario: HTTP session with pooling\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` with `pool_connections` and `pool_maxsize` defaulting to 10\n\n#### Scenario: Token from file\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(file_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return file contents stripped, or empty string on `FileNotFoundError`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configure SDK package metadata\n\nThe system SHALL configure `pyproject.toml` with package metadata, dependencies, and build configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Package configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n- **WHEN** the package is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare package name `agentcube-sdk`, `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`, dependencies including `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, and `cryptography`, build backend `setuptools.build_meta`, and package discovery for `agentcube*` modules\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer application\n\nThe system SHALL create a FastAPI application under `example/pcap-analyzer/` that uses AgentCube code interpreters for PCAP analysis.\n\n#### Scenario: Application structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n- **WHEN** the example application is structured\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer core classes\n\nThe system SHALL implement `SandboxRunner`, agent builders, and analysis orchestration functions in `pcap_analyzer.py`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxRunner operations\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` instance\n- **WHEN** methods are called\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`, `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)`, `run(command)`, and `stop()` methods\n\n#### Scenario: Agent builders\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` imports\n- **WHEN** agent builders are called\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)`, `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text)`, `build_planner_agent(llm)`, and `build_reporter_agent(llm)` functions\n\n#### Scenario: Analysis orchestration\n\n- **GIVEN** analysis functions\n- **WHEN** PCAP analysis is performed\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide `_plan_script`, `_repair_script`, `_execute_once_in_runner`, `_analyze_with_retries`, and `_report` functions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer endpoints\n\nThe system SHALL implement FastAPI endpoints for startup validation and PCAP analysis.\n\n#### Scenario: Startup validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` startup event\n- **WHEN** the application starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail if `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or configured API key) is not available, and build `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents\n\n#### Scenario: Analyze endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `POST /analyze` endpoint\n- **WHEN** called with either `pcap_file: UploadFile` or `pcap_path: str` form field\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configure PCAP analyzer environment\n\nThe system SHALL configure environment variable bindings for OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Environment configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` configuration\n- **WHEN** the service starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL read `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_BASE` (default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`), `OPENAI_MODEL` (default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`), `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` (default `my-interpreter`), `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` (default `default`), and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` (default `5`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with all required Python dependencies.\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency list\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, and the full LangChain/LangGraph stack with pinned versions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n\nThe system SHALL create a Dockerfile that builds the PCAP analyzer image with `uv` and vendors the agentcube SDK.\n\n#### Scenario: Image build\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL use base `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, run `uv venv`, install dependencies with `uv pip install`, copy `sdk-python/agentcube` to `./agentcube/`, copy `pcap_analyzer.py` to root, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port 8000, and set `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n\nThe system SHALL create `deployment.yaml` with Deployment manifest for the analyzer.\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment manifest\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n- **WHEN** applied to cluster\n- **THEN** it SHALL create `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`, run container `pcap-analyzer` with image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, listen on TCP 8000, set resource requests `cpu: 200m` and `memory: 100Mi` with limits `cpu: 1` and `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets`, and set environment variables for all API and sandbox parameters\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create plugin documentation\n\nThe system SHALL create `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore` for the Dify plugin.\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation files exist\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n- **WHEN** documentation is complete\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `GUIDE.md` with usage instructions, `README.md` with project overview, `PRIVACY.md` with privacy policy, and `.difyignore` with packaging exclusions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer README\n\nThe system SHALL create `README.md` for the PCAP analyzer example.\n\n#### Scenario: Example documentation exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n- **WHEN** documentation is complete\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `README.md` with setup, usage, and deployment instructions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Ensure session header naming\n\nThe system SHALL ensure all SDK Router requests use the lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: Session header consistency\n\n- **GIVEN** SDK data plane clients\n- **WHEN** making Router requests\n- **THEN** both `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use header `x-agentcube-session-id` (with appropriate casing for the constant name)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Ensure timeout defaults\n\nThe system SHALL ensure control-plane and data-plane clients default to 120-second read timeout and 5-second connect timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout defaults applied\n\n- **GIVEN** client initialization\n- **WHEN** no custom timeouts are provided\n- **THEN** `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Handle router URL environment variable\n\nThe system SHALL ensure `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` resolve `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable.\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL resolution\n\n- **GIVEN** client instantiation\n- **WHEN** `router_url` is not provided as argument\n- **THEN** both clients SHALL read from `ROUTER_URL` environment variable and raise `ValueError` if not set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Handle workload manager URL and auth token\n\nThe system SHALL ensure `ControlPlaneClient` resolves `workload_manager_url` from argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env, and `auth_token` from argument or SA token file.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation\n- **WHEN** `workload_manager_url` is not provided\n- **THEN** it SHALL read from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token resolution\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file` and set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header if token is non-empty","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775888313747,"end":1775888313754}}}}
