{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888326527,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b315f5a001ldcqkxmLGNEEbq","messageID":"msg_d7b312dcb001XIHrDjgmuLUSum","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-37bd7c0b47b34cb39ff14af35ce27c75","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-029\n5: - **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n6: - **Module**: sdk-python\n7: - **Language**: Python\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: This delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\n17: The system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n20: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n21: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n22: - **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n25: - **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n26: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n27: - **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n30: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n31: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n32: - **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n35: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n36: - **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n37: - **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\n40: The system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n43: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n44: - **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n45: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n48: - **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n49: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n50: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n53: - **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n54: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n55: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\n58: The system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Delete session success\n61: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n62: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n63: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n66: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n67: - **WHEN** the response is received\n68: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n71: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n72: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n73: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\n76: The system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n79: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n80: - **WHEN** requests are made\n81: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n84: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n85: - **WHEN** requests are made\n86: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n89: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n90: - **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n91: - **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n94: The system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n97: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n98: - **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n99: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n102: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n103: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n104: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n105: \n106: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\n107: The system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Request includes session header\n110: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n111: - **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n112: - **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n115: - **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n116: - **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n117: - **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n120: - **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n121: - **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n122: - **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\n125: The system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n128: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n129: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n130: - **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n133: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n134: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n135: - **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n136: \n137: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\n138: The system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n141: - **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n142: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n143: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n146: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n147: - **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n148: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n151: - **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n152: - **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n153: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: List files in directory\n156: - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n157: - **WHEN** the request completes\n158: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n161: The system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n164: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n165: - **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n166: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\n169: The system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n172: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n173: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n174: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n177: - **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n178: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n179: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\n182: The system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n185: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n186: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n187: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n190: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n191: - **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n192: - **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n195: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n196: - **WHEN** the method executes\n197: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\n200: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n203: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n204: - **WHEN** the session is created\n205: - **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n208: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n209: - **WHEN** the session is created\n210: - **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n213: - **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n214: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n215: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n216: \n217: ### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\n218: The system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n221: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n222: - **WHEN** the block exits\n223: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n226: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n227: - **WHEN** the block exits\n228: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n231: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n232: - **WHEN** the block exits\n233: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n234: \n235: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\n236: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n239: - **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n240: - **WHEN** the error is raised\n241: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n244: - **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n245: - **WHEN** the error is raised\n246: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n247: \n248: ### Requirement: Token file reading utility\n249: The system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Read existing token file\n252: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n253: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n254: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n257: - **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n258: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n260: \n261: ### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\n262: The system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n265: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n266: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n267: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n270: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n271: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n273: \n274: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n275: \n276: 1. ✅ ControlPlaneClient resolves environment variables for base_url and auth_token\n277: 2. ✅ ControlPlaneClient creates sessions via POST with proper headers and JSON body\n278: 3. ✅ ControlPlaneClient deletes sessions via DELETE with 404 tolerance\n279: 4. ✅ ControlPlaneClient uses configurable timeouts and connection pooling\n280: 5. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name\n281: 6. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient injects x-agentcube-session-id header in all requests\n282: 7. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient executes commands with timeout buffer to avoid ReadTimeout\n283: 8. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient supports write, upload, download, and list file operations\n284: 9. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name\n285: 10. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstraps session ID via GET request\n286: 11. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invokes workloads via POST with JSON payload\n287: 12. ✅ HTTP session management uses requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n288: 13. ✅ Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n289: 14. ✅ Exception hierarchy defines AgentCubeError, SessionError, and DataPlaneError\n290: 15. ✅ Token file reading utility reads Kubernetes service account tokens\n291: 16. ✅ Logger configuration utility provides consistent logger setup\n292: \n293: ## Dependencies\n294: \n295: - `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n296: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n297: - `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n298: - Python >=3.10\n299: \n300: ## References\n301: \n302: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n303: - Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n304: - AR: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n(End of file - total 304 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775888326515,"end":1775888326524}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775888326558,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b315f7e001SDubEElYsTY7V4","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b312dcb001XIHrDjgmuLUSum","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":32603,"input":17480,"output":84,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15039}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775888328818,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b316871001wN7Y7OUL0NCfE8","messageID":"msg_d7b315fbf001hMtXKWUFhqsGHh","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775888433396,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b317d8a001F5o8SqUcOlNc8R","messageID":"msg_d7b315fbf001hMtXKWUFhqsGHh","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","type":"text","text":"The file already contains content for AR-029. I'll overwrite it with the delta spec for AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 as specified in the prompt.","time":{"start":1775888433393,"end":1775888433393}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888433569,"sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3300f5001BDMr8fldpSykRU","messageID":"msg_d7b315fbf001hMtXKWUFhqsGHh","sessionID":"ses_284cfd0cfffeech7ADWvVAwtEY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3dce8f36c6b947e599b97c2b4745339d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification — AR-036 Dify Plugin Integration\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-036\n- **Title**: Dify 插件集成\n- **Module**: integrations\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplementation deltas for adding Dify plugin integration to the AgentCube project, including the Python SDK client library and PCAP analyzer example application.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Create Dify plugin package structure\n\nThe system SHALL create a complete Dify plugin package under `integrations/dify-plugin/` with all required manifest files, provider descriptors, tool definitions, and Python implementations.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin directory layout exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a new `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n- **WHEN** the package structure is created\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement plugin manifest\n\nThe system SHALL implement `manifest.yaml` with all required fields including version, type, author, name, multilingual labels/descriptions, icons, resource permissions, tool provider references, and runner metadata.\n\n#### Scenario: Manifest contains all required fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the file is parsed by Dify toolchain\n- **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version: 0.0.2`, `type: plugin`, `author: volcano-sh`, `name: agentcube`, `label` with multilingual map for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR`, `description` with multilingual strings, `icon: icon.png`, `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`, `resource` subtree with `memory` and `permission` flags, `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`, and `meta` with `version`, `arch` (amd64, arm64), `runner` (language: python, version: \"3.12\", entrypoint: main), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement provider descriptor\n\nThe system SHALL implement `provider/agentcube.yaml` with identity fields and tool list pointing to the code interpreter tool.\n\n#### Scenario: Provider descriptor structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the provider is loaded by Dify\n- **THEN** the file SHALL contain `identity` with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label`, multilingual `description`, `icon`, a `tools` list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement tool schema\n\nThe system SHALL implement `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` with the complete parameter schema for the code interpreter integration.\n\n#### Scenario: Tool parameter schema\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the tool is configured in Dify\n- **THEN** the schema SHALL define `identity` with `name: agentcube-code-interpreter`, `author: agentcube`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `parameters` array with `router_url` (string, required, form), `workload_manager_url` (string, required, form), `language` (select, options: python, javascript, typescript, llm), `code` (string, llm), `command` (string, llm), `session_id` (string, llm), `session_reuse` (boolean, llm), and `code_interpreter_id` (string, llm), each with `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, and `form` fields\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement plugin main entry\n\nThe system SHALL implement `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a 120-second request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n- **WHEN** Dify starts the plugin\n- **THEN** the file SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement provider class\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class that extends `ToolProvider` with credential validation.\n\n#### Scenario: Provider class structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n- **WHEN** the provider class is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)` with `_validate_credentials` method that may raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement tool class\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` class that extends `Tool` and delegates to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: Tool class invocation\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n- **WHEN** Dify invokes the tool\n- **THEN** the class SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)` with `_invoke` method that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`, and an `execute` method accepting `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`, and delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create plugin dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with pinned versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk`.\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n- **THEN** the file SHALL contain `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create Python SDK package\n\nThe system SHALL create the complete `agentcube-sdk` Python package under `sdk-python/` with all client classes and utilities.\n\n#### Scenario: SDK package layout\n\n- **GIVEN** `sdk-python/` directory\n- **WHEN** the SDK is structured\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `pyproject.toml`, `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/exceptions.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/utils/http.py`, `agentcube/utils/utils.py`, `agentcube/utils/log.py`, and `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterClient` with session management, file operations, code execution, and command execution.\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL accept `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url` (or from `ROUTER_URL` env), `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id`, initialize `ControlPlaneClient` and `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and raise `ValueError` if `router_url` is not provided\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance used as context manager\n- **WHEN** the context exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` which closes the data plane session, deletes the control plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Command execution with non-zero exit\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called\n- **WHEN** the remote command returns `exit_code != 0`\n- **THEN** the method SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` as `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n- **WHEN** the code is executed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` with session bootstrap, invocation, and lifecycle management.\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization and session bootstrap\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated without `session_id`\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`, raising `ValueError` if the header is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session\n\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance with falsy `session_id`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement ControlPlaneClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `ControlPlaneClient` with session creation and deletion via the Workload Manager API.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session\n\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, and `metadata`, and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session with 404\n\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called and server returns 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with file operations, command execution, and code execution via the Router API.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with timeout buffer\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=<value>)` posts to `api/execute`\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON with `command` array and `timeout` string, and the read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n\n#### Scenario: File write operation\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode: \"0644\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\nThe system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with session bootstrap and invocation via the Router API.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to 120\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement exception hierarchy\n\nThe system SHALL define the complete exception hierarchy in `agentcube/exceptions.py`.\n\n#### Scenario: Exception classes defined\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n- **WHEN** exceptions are imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentCubeError` (base), `CommandExecutionError` (with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`), `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement utility modules\n\nThe system SHALL implement utility modules for HTTP session creation, token reading, and logging.\n\n#### Scenario: HTTP session with pooling\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` with `pool_connections` and `pool_maxsize` defaulting to 10\n\n#### Scenario: Token from file\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(file_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return file contents stripped, or empty string on `FileNotFoundError`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configure SDK package metadata\n\nThe system SHALL configure `pyproject.toml` with package metadata, dependencies, and build configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Package configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n- **WHEN** the package is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare package name `agentcube-sdk`, `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`, dependencies including `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, and `cryptography`, build backend `setuptools.build_meta`, and package discovery for `agentcube*` modules\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer application\n\nThe system SHALL create a FastAPI application under `example/pcap-analyzer/` that uses AgentCube code interpreters for PCAP analysis.\n\n#### Scenario: Application structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n- **WHEN** the example application is structured\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer core classes\n\nThe system SHALL implement `SandboxRunner`, agent builders, and analysis orchestration functions in `pcap_analyzer.py`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxRunner operations\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` instance\n- **WHEN** methods are called\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`, `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)`, `run(command)`, and `stop()` methods\n\n#### Scenario: Agent builders\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` imports\n- **WHEN** agent builders are called\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)`, `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text)`, `build_planner_agent(llm)`, and `build_reporter_agent(llm)` functions\n\n#### Scenario: Analysis orchestration\n\n- **GIVEN** analysis functions\n- **WHEN** PCAP analysis is performed\n- **THEN** it SHALL provide `_plan_script`, `_repair_script`, `_execute_once_in_runner`, `_analyze_with_retries`, and `_report` functions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer endpoints\n\nThe system SHALL implement FastAPI endpoints for startup validation and PCAP analysis.\n\n#### Scenario: Startup validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` startup event\n- **WHEN** the application starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail if `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or configured API key) is not available, and build `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents\n\n#### Scenario: Analyze endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `POST /analyze` endpoint\n- **WHEN** called with either `pcap_file: UploadFile` or `pcap_path: str` form field\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configure PCAP analyzer environment\n\nThe system SHALL configure environment variable bindings for OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Environment configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` configuration\n- **WHEN** the service starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL read `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_BASE` (default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`), `OPENAI_MODEL` (default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`), `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` (default `my-interpreter`), `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` (default `default`), and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` (default `5`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with all required Python dependencies.\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency list\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, and the full LangChain/LangGraph stack with pinned versions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n\nThe system SHALL create a Dockerfile that builds the PCAP analyzer image with `uv` and vendors the agentcube SDK.\n\n#### Scenario: Image build\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL use base `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, run `uv venv`, install dependencies with `uv pip install`, copy `sdk-python/agentcube` to `./agentcube/`, copy `pcap_analyzer.py` to root, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port 8000, and set `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n\nThe system SHALL create `deployment.yaml` with Deployment manifest for the analyzer.\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment manifest\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n- **WHEN** applied to cluster\n- **THEN** it SHALL create `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`, run container `pcap-analyzer` with image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, listen on TCP 8000, set resource requests `cpu: 200m` and `memory: 100Mi` with limits `cpu: 1` and `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets`, and set environment variables for all API and sandbox parameters\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create plugin documentation\n\nThe system SHALL create `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore` for the Dify plugin.\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation files exist\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n- **WHEN** documentation is complete\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `GUIDE.md` with usage instructions, `README.md` with project overview, `PRIVACY.md` with privacy policy, and `.difyignore` with packaging exclusions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer README\n\nThe system SHALL create `README.md` for the PCAP analyzer example.\n\n#### Scenario: Example documentation exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n- **WHEN** documentation is complete\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `README.md` with setup, usage, and deployment instructions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Ensure session header naming\n\nThe system SHALL ensure all SDK Router requests use the lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: Session header consistency\n\n- **GIVEN** SDK data plane clients\n- **WHEN** making Router requests\n- **THEN** both `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use header `x-agentcube-session-id` (with appropriate casing for the constant name)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Ensure timeout defaults\n\nThe system SHALL ensure control-plane and data-plane clients default to 120-second read timeout and 5-second connect timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout defaults applied\n\n- **GIVEN** client initialization\n- **WHEN** no custom timeouts are provided\n- **THEN** `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Handle router URL environment variable\n\nThe system SHALL ensure `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` resolve `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable.\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL resolution\n\n- **GIVEN** client instantiation\n- **WHEN** `router_url` is not provided as argument\n- **THEN** both clients SHALL read from `ROUTER_URL` environment variable and raise `ValueError` if not set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Handle workload manager URL and auth token\n\nThe system SHALL ensure `ControlPlaneClient` resolves `workload_manager_url` from argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env, and `auth_token` from argument or SA token file.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation\n- **WHEN** `workload_manager_url` is not provided\n- **THEN** it SHALL read from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token resolution\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file` and set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header if token is non-empty\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Dify plugin package structure created with all required files\n2. ✅ Plugin manifest includes all required fields\n3. ✅ Provider descriptor properly configured\n4. ✅ Tool schema with complete parameter definitions\n5. ✅ Plugin main entry point runs Dify framework\n6. ✅ Provider class with credential validation\n7. ✅ Tool class delegates to agentcube SDK\n8. ✅ Plugin dependencies pinned correctly\n9. ✅ Python SDK package structure complete\n10. ✅ CodeInterpreterClient implements session management\n11. ✅ AgentRuntimeClient implements session bootstrap and invocation\n12. ✅ ControlPlaneClient implements session CRUD operations\n13. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient implements file and command operations\n14. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implements invocation with session management\n15. ✅ Exception hierarchy defined\n16. ✅ Utility modules for HTTP, token, and logging\n17. ✅ SDK package metadata configured\n18. ✅ PCAP analyzer application structure\n19. ✅ PCAP analyzer core classes and orchestration\n20. ✅ PCAP analyzer FastAPI endpoints\n21. ✅ PCAP analyzer environment configuration\n22. ✅ PCAP analyzer dependencies specified\n23. ✅ PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n24. ✅ PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n25. ✅ Plugin documentation files\n26. ✅ PCAP analyzer documentation\n27. ✅ Session header naming consistent\n28. ✅ Timeout defaults applied\n29. ✅ Router URL environment variable handling\n30. ✅ Workload manager URL and auth token handling\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n- `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n- `requests`\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0`\n- `cryptography`\n- `fastapi==0.120.0`\n- `uvicorn==0.38.0`\n- LangChain/LangGraph stack\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `integrations/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `integrations/spec.md`\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775888433479,"end":1775888433566}}}}
